article.description: — Jordan Dingle scored 22 points and Pennsylvania defeated Lafayette 74-68 in overtime on Tuesday.
article.headline: Dingle leads Pennsylvania over Lafayette 74-68 in overtime
article.linkText: Dingle leads Pennsylvania over Lafayette 74-68 in overtime
article.story: EASTON, Pa. -- — Jordan Dingle scored 22 points and Pennsylvania defeated Lafayette 74-68 in overtime on Tuesday. Dingle made just 6 of 18 shots from the floor but he was 8-for-8 at the foul line for the Quakers (2-4). Max Martz added 18 points and eight rebounds. Michael Moshkovitz scored 10. The Leopards (1-5) were led by Leo O'Boyle's 16 points. Jon Brantley added 13 points for Lafayette. CJ Fulton had 12 points, seven rebounds and seven assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
